        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.express.security.audit.express-check-csurf-middleware-usage.express-check-csurf-middleware-usage",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[HIGH] The Express application does not appear to implement Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) protection middleware. Without proper CSRF tokens or other validation for state-changing operations (like POST, PUT, DELETE), an attacker could craft a malicious website that forces authenticated users to unknowingly submit requests to the application, performing unauthorized actions on their behalf.\n\nExploit: An attacker could send a victim a link to a malicious page. If the victim is logged into the vulnerable application, the malicious page could contain an HTML form that automatically submits a POST request to `/change-password` with new password values, causing the victim's password to be changed without their knowledge or consent.\n\nFix: Implementing `csurf` middleware generates and validates a CSRF token for each request. This ensures that state-changing requests originate from the legitimate application interface, as the attacker's site would not have access to a valid token. The fix assumes proper integration of `res.locals.csrfToken` into relevant forms/views."
          },
