        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.mysql.node-mysql-hardcoded-secret.node-mysql-hardcoded-secret",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] Database credentials, specifically the password (`DB_PASSWORD`), are hard-coded directly within the application's source code. This is a severe security risk as it exposes sensitive authentication information. If the source code repository is compromised, or the application bundle is reverse-engineered, attackers can gain direct access to the database.\n\nExploit: An attacker who gains access to the source code (e.g., via a public Git repository, a leaked build artifact) can extract the hard-coded `DB_PASSWORD`. They can then use these credentials to directly connect to the database from any client, potentially accessing, modifying, or deleting all data, or even gaining shell access depending on database privileges.\n\nFix: Retrieving the database password from an environment variable (`process.env.DB_PASSWORD`) prevents it from being hard-coded in the source code. This approach allows credentials to be managed securely outside the application's codebase, reducing the risk of exposure and enabling easier rotation."
