        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.express.security.injection.raw-html-format.raw-html-format",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[HIGH] User-controlled input from `req.query.q` is directly embedded into the HTML response body (`<h1>...</h1>`) without proper HTML encoding. This allows an attacker to inject arbitrary HTML or client-side scripts, leading to a reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerability.\n\nExploit: An attacker can craft a URL like `/search?q=<script>alert(document.cookie)</script>`. When a victim visits this URL, the injected JavaScript will execute in their browser, potentially leading to session hijacking, defacement, or redirection to malicious sites.\n\nFix: By applying an HTML escaping function (e.g., `escapeHtml` from a library like `escape-goat`) to the `query` parameter before it's rendered in the HTML response, special characters (`<`, `>`, `&`, `\"`, `'`) are converted into their corresponding HTML entities. This ensures the browser interprets the user-supplied input as plain text rather than active HTML or JavaScript, effectively neutralizing XSS attacks."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
                "region": {
