        {
          "ruleId": "javascript.jsonwebtoken.security.jwt-none-alg.jwt-none-alg",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The `jwt.verify` function is explicitly configured to accept the `none` algorithm, effectively bypassing all integrity checks of the JWT token. The `none` algorithm means there is no signature to verify, allowing an attacker to craft any token payload (e.g., impersonating any user, elevating privileges) by setting the 'alg' header to 'none' and the application will validate it as legitimate.\n\nExploit: An attacker can forge a token such as `eyJhbGciOiJub25lIn0.eyJ1c2VySWQiOiJhZG1pbiIsImlzQWRtaW4iOnRydWV9.` by setting the `alg` header to `none`. Since the application explicitly allows the `none` algorithm, it will accept this token as valid, even though it has no signature, allowing the attacker to impersonate an administrator or any other user.\n\nFix: Remove `none` from the allowed algorithms list. Always specify strong, cryptographic algorithms (e.g., `HS256`, `RS256`, `ES256`) that were used to sign the token. Additionally, ensure a strong, randomly generated secret key is used for verification, loaded from a secure source like environment variables (`process.env.JWT_SECRET`), not hardcoded or an empty string. This ensures the token's integrity is properly verified."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 129
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Remove `none` from the allowed algorithms list. Always specify strong, cryptographic algorithms (e.g., `HS256`, `RS256`, `ES256`) that were used to sign the token. Additionally, ensure a strong, randomly generated secret key is used for verification, loaded from a secure source like environment variables (`process.env.JWT_SECRET`), not hardcoded or an empty string. This ensures the token's integrity is properly verified."
              },
              "artifactChanges": [
                {
                  "artifactLocation": {
                    "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                    "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                  },
                  "replacements": [
                    {
                      "deletedRegion": {
                        "startLine": 129
                      },
                      "insertedContent": {
                        "text": "  // Ensure a strong, secret key is used from environment variables.\n  // Do not allow 'none' and specify the actual algorithm(s) used for signing.\n  const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET, {\n    algorithms: ['HS256'] // Example: Use HS256 or RS256, but never 'none'.\n  })"
                      }
                    }
                  ]
                }
