            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application uses a hard-coded `DB_PASSWORD` variable to establish a database connection. This practice is insecure because if the code repository or deployment environment is compromised, the database password will be exposed, granting an attacker direct access to the database.\n\nExploit: If `DB_PASSWORD` is literally hard-coded in the source code or an easily accessible configuration file, an attacker who gains access to the source code repository can directly retrieve the database password. A system compromise could also expose environment variables if they are not securely managed.\n\nFix: Database credentials, especially passwords, must never be hard-coded directly into the application source code. Instead, they should be loaded securely from environment variables (e.g., `process.env.DB_PASSWORD`) or a dedicated secret management system. This prevents sensitive information from being exposed if the source code is compromised and allows for easier rotation of credentials without code changes."
