        {
          "ruleId": "javascript_lang_http_url_using_user_input",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[CRITICAL] The application is vulnerable to Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) because it constructs an HTTP POST request using a URL directly provided by the user in the request body (`req.body.url`). An attacker can manipulate this URL to make the server send requests to arbitrary internal or external systems, potentially bypassing network firewalls, probing internal services, or accessing sensitive data.\n\nExploit: An attacker can send a POST request to `/webhook` with a body like `{\"url\": \"http://127.0.0.1/admin\"}` to attempt to access an internal administrative interface, or `{\"url\": \"http://internal-db-server:8080/metrics\"}` to probe for internal service information, or even use `file://` schemes if the HTTP client supports them (though `axios` typically doesn't for `post` requests).\n\nFix: The fix validates the user-provided URL using the built-in `URL` object to ensure it's well-formed and restricts the allowed protocols to only `http:` and `https:`, preventing schemes like `file://`. For stronger security, a whitelist of allowed hostnames should be implemented to ensure requests are only sent to trusted destinations."
          },
          "locations": [
