        {
          "ruleId": "javascript_lang_raw_html_using_user_input",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "[HIGH] The application is vulnerable to Reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) because it directly embeds unsanitized user input (`req.query.q`) into the HTML response. This allows an attacker to inject malicious HTML or JavaScript code that will be executed by the victim's browser when they visit a specially crafted URL.\n\nExploit: An attacker could send a GET request to `/search?q=<script>alert('XSS');</script>` or `/search?q=<img src=x onerror=alert('XSS')>` to execute arbitrary JavaScript in the user's browser, potentially leading to session hijacking, cookie theft, or website defacement.\n\nFix: The fix involves using an HTML escaping library (`escape-html` is a common choice) to convert special HTML characters in the user input (like `<`, `>`, `'`, `\"`, `&`) into their corresponding HTML entities. This prevents the browser from interpreting the input as executable HTML or JavaScript, rendering it as safe plain text instead."
          },
