        {
          "ruleId": "javascript_express_helmet_missing",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "[MEDIUM] The Express application does not utilize Helmet middleware. Helmet is a collection of 15 smaller middleware functions that set various HTTP headers to help protect the application from well-known web vulnerabilities like XSS, clickjacking, insecure connections, and more. Without Helmet, these security headers are not configured by default, potentially exposing users to client-side attacks.\n\nExploit: While not directly exploitable by its absence, missing Helmet means the application lacks defense-in-depth measures. For example, without the `X-Frame-Options` header, the site could be embedded in an iframe for clickjacking attacks. Without `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, browsers might incorrectly guess MIME types, leading to XSS vulnerabilities if malicious content is served.\n\nFix: The fix involves installing the `helmet` package (`npm install helmet`), importing it, and applying it globally to the Express application using `app.use(helmet())`. This automatically configures several important HTTP response headers that enhance security, such as `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, and others, providing defense-in-depth against various web vulnerabilities."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                  "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 24
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "The fix involves installing the `helmet` package (`npm install helmet`), importing it, and applying it globally to the Express application using `app.use(helmet())`. This automatically configures several important HTTP response headers that enhance security, such as `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, and others, providing defense-in-depth against various web vulnerabilities."
              },
              "artifactChanges": [
                {
                  "artifactLocation": {
                    "uri": "src/test-vuln-2.js",
                    "uriBaseId": "%SRCROOT%"
                  },
                  "replacements": [
